SIMPLE: whippletree
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Whippletree
<hw>Whip"ple*tree`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Whip</er>, and cf. <er>Whiffletree</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The pivoted or swinging bar to which the traces, or
tugs, of a harness are fastened, and by which a carriage, a plow, or
other implement or vehicle, is drawn; a whiffletree; a swingletree; a
singletree. See <er>Singletree</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>[People] cut their own <qex>whippletree</qex> in the woodlot.</q>
<rj><qau>Emerson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The cornel tree.</def>
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Whip-poor-will</ent>⟦br⟧
